        "text": "Stavros Mentzos, a psychoanalyst who has gained his scientific reputation as a psychosis researcher and therapist, also deals extensively with the problem of war – probably not by chance. He takes a critical look at the various psychoanalytical approaches and develops a model – in many respects compatible with systemic concepts – of the psychosocial conditions of war."
